exports[`buildPrompt snapshots > await-review json 1`] = `
"You are an autonomous coding agent orchestrating work on the user's repo.

The \`.gtd/\` directory is the workflow's own state (plans, task specs, review
records). Never create, edit, delete, or reference files under \`.gtd/\` — and
never instruct a subagent to — except the specific \`.gtd/\` file this prompt
explicitly tells you to work on. A \`TODO.md\`, \`REVIEW.md\`, or similar file
*outside* \`.gtd/\` is ordinary project code, not workflow state.

\`.gtd/REVIEW.md\` holds the review record for the completed work. This is a human
gate; there is nothing for the agent to do.

Tell the user:

- Read \`.gtd/REVIEW.md\` (and the underlying work it points at).
- To **approve**: run \`gtd step\` with no edits, or only tick checkboxes in
  \`.gtd/REVIEW.md\` — either way ends the review with an approval.
- To **request changes**: write substantive edits or annotations into
  \`.gtd/REVIEW.md\` (or the code) describing what's wrong, then run \`gtd step\` —
  this sends the feedback back for another round.
"
`;

